# {{ cookiecutter.project_name }} — frontend (Nuxt 4 skeleton)

> Minimal Nuxt 4 + Vue 3.6 + TypeScript 6 skeleton. No auth, no UI library, no Pinia — bring your own.
>
> What's wired for you: the Nitro proxy to Django, the OWASP defaults, the Compose service, and the `pnpm-workspace.yaml`.

## Run it

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm dev                          # nuxt on http://localhost:{{ cookiecutter.frontend_dev_port }}
docker compose -f compose.local.yml up   # OR the full stack
```

## What's in the box

```
frontend/
├── package.json    # nuxt 4, vue 3.6, ts 6, eslint — nothing else
├── nuxt.config.ts  # Nitro proxies /api + /_allauth + /static + /media
├── app.vue         # Hello world
├── eslint.config.js
├── tsconfig.json   # extends .nuxt/tsconfig.json
└── .env.example
```

## OWASP Top 10 baseline (already on)

- **A01** — backend authoritative; client guards are UX only
- **A02** — session cookies (HttpOnly) — never JWT in localStorage
- **A03** — Vue auto-escape; `vue/no-v-html` ESLint banned
- **A05** — Nitro proxies keep /api + /_allauth same-origin; no wildcard CORS
- **A06** — `pnpm audit --prod` in CI; pinned majors
- **A08** — `pnpm-lock.yaml` committed
- **A09** — `sourcemap: false` for prod builds

## Adding what you need

```bash
pnpm add @pinia/nuxt pinia                       # state mgmt
pnpm add @nuxtjs/tailwindcss                     # tailwind v4
pnpm add @nuxt/test-utils @playwright/test -D    # testing
pnpm add @nuxtjs/sentry                          # error reporting (opt-in)
```

For auth, copy the Pinia + composable pattern from the [django-bakery Full template](https://github.com/Axionore/Django-Barkery) — it's a typed allauth-headless client with session cookies. Never store tokens in `localStorage`.

## Calling the backend

The Nitro proxy makes `/api/*` and `/_allauth/*` first-party requests. From any composable / page:

```ts
const me = await $fetch("/api/me", { credentials: "include" });
```

If your project uses **Django Ninja** (`api_layer = ninja`), the backend uses `django_auth` — session-based. See [django-ninja auth docs](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/).
If it uses **DRF** (`api_layer = drf`), the backend uses `SessionAuthentication` — see [DRF auth docs](https://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/authentication/).
